node.text:
This year's #Sandhurst Tom Surdyke Leadership Award winner goes to Cadet Ethan Erickson with The College of Saint Benedict Saint John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion.

The award is named in memory of Cadet Thomas Surdyke who died from injuries sustained while saving the life of a drowning stranger. Surdyke was a member of the Company B4 @b4_buffaloes Sandhurst team his Plebe year.

After a long grueling process, five teams were named the top teams of the Sandhurst Military Skills Competition.  During Sandhurst, 44 teams representing four U.S. service academies and 16 ROTC programs compete against one another in a variety of military related contests.

Congratulations to USMA Black who won the overall competition. The top teams are: 

1. USMA Black @usma_sandhurst 
2. USMA Gold
3. Company F1 @f1.firehouse 
4. University of North Georgia @ungcadets 
5. The College of St. Benedict St. John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion

We honor the legacy of Henry O. Flipper for his perseverance and courage to graduate from the U.S. Military Academy and serve in the #USArmy. #Blackhistorymonth

Cadet Leader Development Training (CLDT) tests warrior skills. During a situational training exercise, platoons conduct Air Assault operations and road march to their area of operations. Cadets spent the night in the field conducting patrol base operations and lanes before marching back. During Warrior Week and Cold Load training, trainees reviewed their basic warrior tasks and drills within platoons to prepare for the upcoming 10-day field training exercise, which included battle drills, weapon disassembly and cleaning, planning, briefs, and patrol base operations. During Cold Load Training, cadets do dry runs by boarding and unloading from Blackhawk and Chinook helicopters in preparation for upcoming Air Assault operations.  For more CLDT photos, visit West Point Flickr. #USMA #WestPoint #USMA2022 #USMA2023 #Leadership #GoArmy

Army West Point Athletic Association announces the exciting plans for the fully donor-funded launch of the Michie Stadium Preservation Project. As the home of various Army Black Knight sports programs, the modernization of Michie Stadium, where cadets have watched games since 1962, will include a complete transformation of the East Stands to ensure the most inspirational game-day atmosphere in the country continues. The project will fully integrate the cadets into the reimagination process, to elevate the viewing experience in a way that is authentic to the "Duty, Honor, Country" ideals. For more information, visit: www.michiestadium.com 

@goarmywestpoint #WestPoint #GoArmy #USMA #BeatNavy #GoArmyBeatNavy

U.S. Army Air Assault School is a 10-day course designed to prepare Soldiers for insertion, evacuation, and pathfinder missions that call for the use of multipurpose transportation and assault helicopters.
